# NAVYK Backend Rules

## Architecture Layers (strict)
```
Route Handler (controller)
      ↓
Service Layer (business logic)
      ↓
Repository Layer (Prisma)
      ↓
Database (PostgreSQL)
```

Business logic ONLY in Service. Route handler — parse request, call service, format response. Repository — CRUD only.

## API Response Format
```typescript
// Success
{ success: true, data: T, meta?: { page, limit, total } }

// Error
{ success: false, error: { code: string, message: string, details?: unknown } }
```

## HTTP Statuses
- 200: success (GET, PUT, PATCH)
- 201: created (POST)
- 204: deleted (DELETE)
- 400: validation error
- 401: not authenticated
- 403: forbidden
- 404: not found
- 409: conflict
- 422: business logic error
- 500: server error

## Versioning
All routes: /api/v1/...

## Database (Prisma)
- NEVER edit applied migrations
- Each migration is atomic and reversible
- Migration names describe WHAT changes
- All enum values — uppercase
- Soft delete: deletedAt + isActive for all main entities
- Indexes: all FK fields, WHERE fields, sort fields

## Security
- Sanitize HTML input
- Rate limiting: auth (5 req/min), AI generation (10 req/hour)
- Check ownership before every UPDATE/DELETE
- Passwords: bcrypt cost factor 12
- JWT: access token 15min, refresh token 30 days
- CORS: only allowed origins from .env
